A mirror, yes.

05:06.139 --> 05:08.471
So everyone will feel like
the protagonist.

05:08.600 --> 05:12.889
"Stop for a moment, fragile creature
and consider what you are".

05:13.480 --> 05:17.018
"The Cloud of Unknowing"
by an unknown English mystic.

05:18.401 --> 05:21.689
- I like the mirror idea.
- Sir?

05:21.863 --> 05:23.820
Gianni Letta's here to see you.

05:24.032 --> 05:27.445
- Did we have an appointment?
- No.

05:28.995 --> 05:30.485
I have to go, excuse me.

05:48.181 --> 05:50.013
How are you?

05:50.517 --> 05:52.599
Everything okay?

05:53.728 --> 05:55.139
Yeah.

06:01.152 --> 06:04.065
- Have you had a screw?
- Fuck off!

06:05.031 --> 06:09.616
If Magic Johnson's in the Olympics
then why can't you have a screw?

06:09.786 --> 06:12.949
The Australians have said
they won't play against Magic.

06:13.039 --> 06:15.531
- They're scared of getting AIDS.
- I know.

06:15.625 --> 06:17.992
Did you hear
what Charles Barkley said?

06:18.211 --> 06:19.747
You don't have work to do?

06:21.047 --> 06:22.629
No.

06:23.216 --> 06:25.628
Please, come this way.

06:26.803 --> 06:30.046
- Take a seat, I'll be right there.
- Shit, it's Ligresti.

06:37.606 --> 06:40.644
When we found your villa empty,

06:41.234 --> 06:43.475
we thought
you'd gone back to Sicily.

06:43.695 --> 06:47.108
As you can see, I'm here now.
And I came of my own free will.

06:48.033 --> 06:51.617
Yes, you've taken a few days off
to sort some things out.

06:52.120 --> 06:55.078
The industrialists are talking,
Ligresti.

06:55.832 --> 07:00.167
- It's the end of an era.
- Di Pietro...

07:01.046 --> 07:06.587
You're in the headlines now,
you feel loved by the people, powerful!

07:07.260 --> 07:10.469
So you keep making
the investigation bigger.

07:10.972 --> 07:13.760
But one of these days,
by casting the net further,

07:13.850 --> 07:16.638
you'll catch the small fish too.

07:17.020 --> 07:20.934
When the Italians realize
Clean Hands is homing in on them,

07:21.107 --> 07:24.691
on that day,
you and your colleagues...

07:25.236 --> 07:30.697
will end up alone,
from one moment to the next.

07:31.576 --> 07:34.739
And things will go back
to the way they were in Italy.

07:36.039 --> 07:38.030
Don't you believe me?

07:38.249 --> 07:40.616
Do you want to bet?

07:41.127 --> 07:44.245
Let's do this: you take this

07:45.048 --> 07:49.337
and return it to me when you explain
your business with Craxi.

07:52.639 --> 07:57.759
If that's the case,
kiss your precious watch goodbye.

07:59.020 --> 08:01.637
We'll talk about it in San Vittore.

08:03.274 --> 08:05.015
How come
you're going to the airport?

08:05.110 --> 08:06.066
JULY 12th

08:06.152 --> 08:09.019
Because I'm on the mafia's blacklist
along with other judges.

08:09.239 --> 08:11.446
It seems they want to kill us.

08:11.574 --> 08:14.657
Those idiot guards should escort me,
but I don't trust them.

08:14.953 --> 08:17.411
- Are you up to it?
- Yes.

08:17.622 --> 08:20.410
- Are you scared?
- No.

08:21.501 --> 08:22.912
Hi, Di Pietro.

08:23.169 --> 08:26.036
Schifani worked with Falcone,
and he's dead.

08:28.174 --> 08:31.257
- The watch you gave to Ligresti...
- It's fake.

08:31.553 --> 08:35.217
We seized a load of them
six months ago.

08:36.558 --> 08:38.390
What if Ligresti's right?

08:39.227 --> 08:42.219
Davigo already tried to nab them
six years ago.

08:42.397 --> 08:46.356
They never end up paying,
they always find a way out,

08:46.609 --> 08:49.647
and we work our asses off,
will it pay off?

08:49.821 --> 08:51.653
- Yes.
- Will they win?

08:51.823 --> 08:54.315
- No.
- No, yes, you're so damn eloquent!

08:54.576 --> 08:57.910
First you resign,
then you volunteer...

08:58.121 --> 09:00.453
I can't figure you out, dammit!

09:21.394 --> 09:22.509
Hi

09:23.438 --> 09:25.975
Is this where I sign up
for Actor's Studio?

09:26.191 --> 09:28.228
- Giuliano.
- Veronica.

09:28.610 --> 09:30.567
You're interested in the method?

09:30.653 --> 09:33.941
I've been told that to be an actress
I need to learn to act.

09:34.032 --> 09:38.651
- Have any experience?
- No, but my mother was an actress.

09:38.870 --> 09:40.702
Your mother? What's her name?

09:41.039 --> 09:43.030
You don't know her.

09:43.625 --> 09:45.616
She did experimental theatre.

09:45.835 --> 09:48.827
You make it sound
like it's something weird.

09:50.381 --> 09:51.792
So, how much is it?

09:52.300 --> 09:57.170
"At very high temperature, such
ionizing radiation from depleted uranium

09:57.347 --> 10:01.011
can modify the structure
and emit neutrons".

10:01.643 --> 10:04.226
- Ionizing radiation.
- Yes.

10:04.395 --> 10:08.389
You can't just say
your usual bullshit!

10:09.234 --> 10:11.566
It's all written here.

10:20.411 --> 10:22.368
Hi.

10:22.580 --> 10:26.164
He's Massimo, an old friend.
She's Veronica.

10:27.877 --> 10:28.992
Hi.

10:32.590 --> 10:34.376
Not too shabby, Pietro Bosco!

10:34.634 --> 10:38.218
I get cancer and you get to screw
that hot babe?

10:38.388 --> 10:40.629
Keep your goddamn voice down!

10:41.850 --> 10:44.387
- Give me that paper.
- Here.

10:53.027 --> 10:55.314
I signed up for an acting course.

10:56.531 --> 10:58.397
A serious one.

10:58.658 --> 11:01.025
It's American,
run by the Actor's Studio.

11:03.246 --> 11:04.577
Okay.

11:07.792 --> 11:09.533
Fine, bye.

11:10.587 --> 11:12.043
Wait!

11:14.591 --> 11:16.377
Fucking hell!

11:17.051 --> 11:21.636
It's good. If that's what
you want to do, that's good.

11:22.932 --> 11:25.219
It's expensive, I'm warning you.

11:25.393 --> 11:27.760
How much?

11:33.985 --> 11:35.646
Here.

11:39.032 --> 11:41.649
Two million liras?

11:46.831 --> 11:48.572
<i>Pass me a pen.</i>

12:02.388 --> 12:03.924
I have bad news for us.

12:04.015 --> 12:08.054
Fininvest found out about
your forays in Rome

12:08.228 --> 12:10.014
and your meeting with Segni.

12:10.230 --> 12:12.312
They want to close
the Study Campus.

12:13.233 --> 12:15.019
What?

12:15.401 --> 12:19.019
"Politics is not within
Publitalia's jurisdiction".

12:20.156 --> 12:21.646
What?

12:21.824 --> 12:26.034
Advertisers have increased in numbers
since the Study Campus opened.

12:26.246 --> 12:27.828
What's this about?

12:28.039 --> 12:31.623
For the agency, backing this project
is a waste of money,

12:31.834 --> 12:34.622
so as of tomorrow,
your office is closed.

12:34.837 --> 12:38.250
Those who've come from Publitalia
will remain within the group,

12:38.383 --> 12:42.843
the others, many thanks,
will receive adequate compensation.

12:43.054 --> 12:45.762
- What's Berlusconi saying?
- What do you think?

12:46.391 --> 12:48.632
It's his decision.

12:48.851 --> 12:51.092
Get me an appointment with him.

12:51.312 --> 12:54.395
Even just for 5 minutes,
I'll get him to change his mind...

12:54.649 --> 12:57.562
He's on holiday,
he's enjoying Milan's victory

12:57.652 --> 12:59.188
and he wants to be left in peace.

12:59.279 --> 13:01.816
I'm sorry, that's the way it is.

13:10.665 --> 13:12.326
What a shame.

13:25.388 --> 13:29.097
- <i>Hello?</i>
- Viola, you want to go on holiday?

13:48.036 --> 13:50.403
I think you've forgotten where it is.

13:50.830 --> 13:53.697
When I came here 10 years ago,
there was nothing.

13:54.959 --> 13:57.621
You sound like an old man,
I'm telling you.

13:58.963 --> 13:59.919
There it is!

14:13.144 --> 14:14.851
Amanda!

14:15.730 --> 14:19.223
Hi! Welcome!

14:22.820 --> 14:24.857
- How are you?
- You look beautiful.

14:24.989 --> 14:27.321
- Thanks.
- Sorry for calling out of the blue.

14:27.367 --> 14:29.404
Don't be, it's a pleasure!

14:29.702 --> 14:31.818
- Sit down.
- Thank you.

14:32.038 --> 14:34.871
Shall I get your annexe ready?

14:35.625 --> 14:39.835
- You're sure it's no trouble?
- Sure! Stay as long as you like.

14:40.046 --> 14:42.583
It's a real pleasure for me.

14:43.633 --> 14:46.045
You've not changed, that's for sure.

14:48.638 --> 14:51.972
- Mum, I'm going out. I need money.
- Good evening!

14:52.141 --> 14:55.850
My daughter, Angelica.
That's right, I have a daughter.

14:56.020 --> 14:57.852
She looks just like you.

14:58.022 --> 15:01.356
Here. Only horribly younger.

15:03.194 --> 15:05.310
- How old are you?
- 15.

15:05.530 --> 15:08.238
It's a challenge
having a daughter that age.

15:08.408 --> 15:10.695
- I'm going, bye.
- Bye!

15:11.035 --> 15:12.696
I can imagine.

15:13.413 --> 15:15.029
Viola, my daughter.

15:15.748 --> 15:18.786
- Can you add an extra bed?
- Of course.

15:20.002 --> 15:22.334
- Hello, my dear.
- This is Amanda.

15:22.672 --> 15:24.003
Sit down.

15:31.389 --> 15:35.098
You called me for this? I hoped
you'd tell me Di Pietro's fate.

15:35.226 --> 15:37.968
I've got Beatrice Mainaghi,
ready to ruin her father.

15:38.020 --> 15:40.307
Isn't that enough?

15:40.648 --> 15:42.855
This blood story is a real scoop.

15:43.025 --> 15:44.857
How did you find out?

15:45.653 --> 15:49.396
A friend of mine contracted AIDS
via a blood transfusion.

15:49.824 --> 15:54.614
He tried suing them, it was tough,
so I gave him a hand.

15:54.704 --> 15:58.163
I found an informer at Zenit
who confirmed the story.

15:58.416 --> 16:01.033
The blood comes from America.

16:01.252 --> 16:04.210
The donors are prisoners
from Arkansas.

16:04.380 --> 16:08.089
Zenit bought their blood cheaply
and didn't test it.

16:08.593 --> 16:12.587
They used it to make blood products
to sell to the State

16:12.805 --> 16:15.297
who distributed them to hospitals.

16:17.226 --> 16:19.308
Is Beatrice Mainaghi your informer?

16:19.395 --> 16:22.854
No, it's someone
from the buyers' sector.

16:23.649 --> 16:26.357
I spoke to him, then he disappeared.

16:26.611 --> 16:27.976
Do you trust her?

16:28.613 --> 16:33.403
She said she'll give you free access
to Zenit's archives, she seems honest.

16:34.243 --> 16:36.450
How did you persuade her?

16:38.039 --> 16:40.326
Do you want to do
this interview or not?

16:49.926 --> 16:53.760
- Will you get the boxes?
- Yes.

17:05.566 --> 17:09.776
Isn't it creepy coming to live
where your father died?

17:09.945 --> 17:10.902
No.

17:11.405 --> 17:13.988
- You're brave.
- Very brave!

17:14.534 --> 17:17.026
I spoke to my journalist friend,

17:17.244 --> 17:20.032
she's willing to interview you.

17:21.790 --> 17:23.156
What should I say?

17:23.251 --> 17:26.618
That you want the truth
about that blood too

17:26.837 --> 17:28.999
and that you weren't involved.

17:32.051 --> 17:34.383
You're sure you want to do it?

17:35.388 --> 17:37.925
Are you sure it's his fault?

17:38.933 --> 17:40.048
Yes.

17:40.851 --> 17:42.512
All right.

17:44.397 --> 17:46.229
Everyone will hate you.

17:46.399 --> 17:51.610
My brother already hates me
because he thinks I stole his job.

17:58.244 --> 18:00.576
What documents do you need?

18:06.961 --> 18:12.377
Today the committee is gathered
with the Defense Minister, Salvo Andi).

18:16.304 --> 18:19.296
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

18:24.270 --> 18:29.310
Today's agenda deals with
the presentation by the minister

18:29.525 --> 18:33.610
of military expenditure items
included in the financial bill.

18:33.821 --> 18:36.654
And about how these
have been articulated

18:36.824 --> 18:40.317
following the recent
parliamentary debate.

18:40.620 --> 18:43.738
Honorable... Bosco.

18:46.834 --> 18:51.704
Instead of talking about money,
let's discuss our soldiers' health.

18:53.507 --> 18:58.252
The Defense Committee should worry
about its soldiers, every so often.

18:58.429 --> 19:00.545
Pass these round.

19:01.307 --> 19:05.050
Many survivors from the Gulf War
have fallen ill.

19:05.645 --> 19:07.181
What are these papers?

19:07.313 --> 19:11.932
A list of the illnesses that NATO soldiers
back from Iraq suffer from.

19:12.318 --> 19:13.900
Take one.

19:14.195 --> 19:17.608
It shows how many American soldiers
fell ill in the past year.

19:17.782 --> 19:20.399
But no one's talking about it here.

19:20.993 --> 19:24.076
We fought alongside them,
our men got ill too.

19:24.288 --> 19:26.154
- Honorable Bosco...
- Our men are ill!

19:26.791 --> 19:29.328
Honorable Bosco, what are you doing?

19:29.502 --> 19:33.245
The minister is here today,
we have to discuss the financial bill.

19:34.632 --> 19:36.794
It's the Presidency's decision.

19:36.884 --> 19:39.876
If you have a question
for the Committee,

19:39.970 --> 19:43.053
we'll include it on the agenda
of the next meeting.

19:43.224 --> 19:45.056
What a drag!

19:45.685 --> 19:48.393
And now, please
gather your paperwork.

19:48.729 --> 19:52.848
No, keep it,
so you can read them for next time.

19:55.403 --> 19:57.394
Go ahead, sir.

19:59.240 --> 20:02.028
Good morning, dear colleagues.

20:05.830 --> 20:08.037
- Mr Bosco?
- Colonel Maggioni...

20:08.249 --> 20:12.038
- May I ask you a question?
- You just did.

20:12.253 --> 20:14.836
- Are you a patriot?
- I'm a Northern League member.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.833
Answer me.

20:17.550 --> 20:19.632
You're a soldier, right?

20:19.844 --> 20:22.632
Only a military man is interested
in soldiers' health.

20:22.805 --> 20:26.844
- So? ls that a problem?
- Regarding these illnesses...

20:27.393 --> 20:31.227
are you sure your sources
of information are reliable?

20:31.397 --> 20:35.641
Shit, I get it. The minister
handed you the note.

20:35.860 --> 20:38.022
You've come to lecture me!

20:39.405 --> 20:43.569
You know why I asked you that?
Because you're no patriot,

20:43.659 --> 20:46.242
you're slinging mud
at the Italian Navy!

20:46.412 --> 20:48.870
Have you been to Iraq?

20:49.415 --> 20:55.036
Swear on your children's lives that
we never used depleted uranium there.

20:55.254 --> 20:57.370
We never used it.

20:58.382 --> 21:01.044
Fuck you!
I bet you don't have children.

21:01.260 --> 21:03.627
If you want answers, ask us.

21:04.847 --> 21:07.054
Don't bring politicians into it.

21:08.017 --> 21:11.226
They don't want to know
what really happens in a war,

21:11.395 --> 21:15.855
and if you tell them,
they'll hate you for it.

21:16.025 --> 21:18.642
You know what war is, they don't.

21:18.819 --> 21:21.982
Dirty laundry shouldn't be aired
in public, right?

21:23.407 --> 21:25.648
You were one of us, Bosco.

21:27.244 --> 21:31.238
Do you really want to disgrace
your family in front of everyone?

22:04.031 --> 22:07.023
I'd only gone to ask
if she wanted some tea.

22:07.243 --> 22:11.407
They were having sex in broad daylight,
with the door wide open.

22:11.622 --> 22:12.657
My mum...

22:14.375 --> 22:16.412
said it was natural.

22:17.753 --> 22:20.370
That there was nothing
to be ashamed of.

22:23.926 --> 22:26.543
His ass... his skinny ass,

22:28.848 --> 22:31.215
moved up and down.

22:31.392 --> 22:33.804
My mother's face...

22:35.020 --> 22:38.229
It looked like she was shouting
even though she was quiet.

22:39.441 --> 22:42.229
At a certain point,
he opened his eyes...

22:42.903 --> 22:44.735
and saw me.

22:45.823 --> 22:47.985
My mother didn't even notice me.

22:48.826 --> 22:50.612
He smiled at me,

22:50.828 --> 22:53.320
he kept screwing her
and smiling at me.

22:54.623 --> 22:56.830
I ran away.

23:00.421 --> 23:02.628
I was always competing with her.

23:03.674 --> 23:06.257
So I wanted to see if he...

23:07.386 --> 23:10.845
if that look of desire
had been real.

23:12.850 --> 23:15.933
So I started messing around with him,

23:16.103 --> 23:18.390
one day when my mum was out.

23:20.649 --> 23:22.856
I hadn't imagined it.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.645
He really did desire me.

23:31.035 --> 23:33.618
I was 13, shit.

23:35.623 --> 23:38.490
You were brilliant, Veronica.

23:49.720 --> 23:54.635
A friend of mine has written
a very courageous, real piece

23:54.934 --> 23:56.845
and wants to bring it to theatre.

23:57.853 --> 24:00.390
Would you like to audition for it?

24:10.157 --> 24:12.023
Are you going out?

24:13.661 --> 24:15.823
Angelica's taking me to a party.

24:16.038 --> 24:17.779
Hey!

24:18.457 --> 24:20.619
No lipstick.

24:23.545 --> 24:26.037
You look like a mini Jessica Rabbit.

24:26.715 --> 24:28.501
Confiscated.

24:35.057 --> 24:36.673
Where did you meet Amanda?

24:37.685 --> 24:39.392
She's an old client of mine.

24:39.645 --> 24:42.387
She owns Lombardy's
biggest textile conglomerate.

24:42.648 --> 24:44.389
She's had some work done.

24:47.236 --> 24:49.227
Getting old is horrible.

25:18.767 --> 25:22.135
I saw a guy wearing
a vest and flip-flops.

25:22.521 --> 25:25.730
- You'll be seeing more of them...
- What can we do?

25:25.816 --> 25:28.399
Shopkeepers have yachts now!

25:34.366 --> 25:36.198
Leo Notte!

25:38.078 --> 25:40.319
- Cool, how are you?
- Looking good.

25:40.372 --> 25:43.080
As always! Hi, how are you?

25:43.333 --> 25:46.121
I'm having a party on Friday.

25:46.253 --> 25:48.665
Loads of babes, will you come?

25:48.881 --> 25:51.088
- If I'm in the area.
- Come!

25:51.675 --> 25:53.837
Don't forget! Bye.

25:58.891 --> 26:04.386
Zeno Mainaghi, talking of
the decadence of the Costa Smeralda.

26:07.399 --> 26:09.185
Right.

26:12.237 --> 26:15.400
You don't need to feel obliged.

26:17.201 --> 26:19.818
You can be my guest all the same.

26:22.039 --> 26:24.622
I remember you being a smart woman.

26:36.428 --> 26:38.419
Turn it on...

26:39.848 --> 26:42.010
Do you also remember...

26:43.393 --> 26:45.384
how beautiful I was?

26:46.105 --> 26:47.891
You're still beautiful.

26:49.024 --> 26:53.643
You're smart, witty, good in bed,
that's what makes you beautiful.

26:53.821 --> 26:56.358
- You're right!
- Turn it on.

26:57.616 --> 26:59.573
I will.

